Isn't it amazing how fashion can reflect both tradition and modern design? This photo showcases just that, with a beautiful blend of classic and contemporary elements. The fiery energy in the picture reminds me of the passion we have for celebrating our heritage while also embracing the new. It's a tribute to the powerful spirit of the modern woman, who can honor her roots while still forging ahead with confidence and style. Let's take a moment to appreciate the beauty of our fire signs and the incredible impact they have on our lives. Here's to fashion that speaks to our souls and inspires us to be our best selves!🔥💕 #FashionStatement #TraditionAndDesign #PowerfulWomen #CelebratingHeritage #newbeginnings

Step 1 : Always use a Comb while straightening your hair because it detangles and smooths the hair at the same time. Moreover, it saves time! 
Step 2 : Always take a small section of your hair when straightening. It prevents heat loss and saves you time! 
Step 3 : Try different angles of the straightener while straightening your hair for a perfect sleek look. For instance as you can see in the Reel, I’m using the vertical and horizontal sides of my hair straightener when doing a section of my hair. 
Step 4 : For a voluminous face framing, use a Round brush and then straighten the front section of your hair. 

That’s all! It usually takes me 30 minutes to straighten my hair using the Steps as mentioned above but it might take you less or more depending on your hair Volume and Length.
